genresAdvancedInfo.name: protest folk
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Protest folk is a genre of music that emerged in the 1960s as a form of political and social commentary. It is characterized by its acoustic instrumentation, simple melodies, and lyrics that address issues such as war, poverty, and civil rights. Protest folk has been used as a tool for activism and social change, and has inspired generations of musicians to use their art to speak out against injustice.
